## DM Notes — Round 4

**Revenant at 0 HP without coffer destroyed:** It collapses, then reforms at **full HP** in 1d4 rounds. Players need to figure this out — give them a DC 10 Arcana check as a free breadcrumb if they seem stuck.

**Coffer destroyed:** Revenant lets out a wail heard through two floors of the dungeon. It takes 6d8 necrotic damage (no save) and loses all regeneration. Its **Corrupting Gaze** recharges and it uses it immediately as a reaction — one last defiant scream.

**Wardens surrender condition:** If the Revenant dies, both Wardens drop to one knee. They do not attack again unless attacked. They were bound to guard it — that contract is broken. *Roleplaying opportunity.*

## Loot (if victorious)

- Iron Coffer (if intact): 320 gp in ancient Nerathi coin, a *ring of water walking*, and a letter in Supernal — *"Forgive me, Celeste."*
- Warden corpses: Each carries a **Funerary Seal** (spell component worth 50 gp, useful for Speak with Dead)

